<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Six `Law Offenders' Executed 10 May Following Trial </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Six `Law Offenders' Executed 10 May Following Trial </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Demonstrates' Resolution </H4>

<F P=102> OW1005124794 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0857 
GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1005124794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Zhang Sutang (1728 1372 1016) ] </F>
  [Excerpts] Beijing, 10 May (XINHUA) -- Liu Jiachen, vice 
president of the Supreme People's Court, made an announcement in 
Beijing today: People's courts in various places have completed 
the trial of four serious cases involving theft and damage to 
railways, oilfields, electric power equipment, and 
communications facilities. Six law offenders were sentenced to 
death and were executed by shooting in Daqing, Liuzhou, 
Zhumadian and Huanggang respectively today. 
  At a news briefing held by the Supreme People's Court, Liu 
Jiachen said: Recently, serious crimes involving theft and 
damage to railways, oilfields, and electric power and 
communications facilities have been rampant. Those criminal 
activities are very harmful to public security, social 
stability, state property, and the smooth building of the 
national economy. The carrying out of the death sentence of the 
six criminals who committed heinous crimes is a demonstration of 
the resolute and forceful struggle against such activities waged 
by the people's courts as state adjudication organizations. 
[passage omitted] 
  After the people's courts passed their initial judgments, 
all 
six criminals appealed. The higher people's courts in 
Heilongjiang, Guangxi, Henan, and Hubei rejected the appeals and 
affirmed the original judgments in their final decisions. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

