<H3> <TI>   NPC Standing Committee Session Examines Draft Laws </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NPC Standing Committee Session Examines Draft Laws </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1005131594 Beijing Central People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1030 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1005131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing Central People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National Hookup" program] </F>
  [Excerpts] Members of the Standing Committee attending the 
Seventh Session of the Standing Committee of the Eighth National 
People's Congress [NPC] today [9 May] examined the Draft Law on 
the Management of Urban Real Estate, the draft decision on 
punishing criminals who violate copyrights, and other proposals. 
[passage omitted] 
  Some members held that laws related to the Law on the 
Management of Urban Real Estate, such as the Land Administration 
Law, should also be formulated as quickly as possible. Some 
members said that, in order to prevent disputes over trifles 
among various real estate administrative departments, it is 
necessary to let one department assume unified management. 
  In examining the draft decision on punishing criminals who 
violate copyrights, some members said that, without clear and 
specific laws and regulations, the people's court will find it 
difficult to make punitive judgments. They eagerly hoped that 
the decision could be adopted after revision as quickly as 
possible. 
  The members today also examined the Draft Law on Judges and 
the Draft Law on Procurators. 

</TEXT>

