<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Internal Trade Minister Stresses Price Stability </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Internal Trade Minister Stresses Price Stability </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1005135894 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1124 GMT 
10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1005135894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 10 (CNS) -- Minister of Internal 
Trade, Mr. Zhang Haoruo, speaking at a meeting recently held by 
the ministry on an analysis of the economic situation in the 
internal trade sector in the country, stressed that the key task 
at present facing the ministry was to stabilize markets and 
prices in the country. All departments and units engaging in 
commodity circulation must take an earnest attitude to the 
inflation problem with special attention being paid to the 
stability of prices of important goods such as grain, edible 
oil, meat, sugar and chemical fertilizers. 
  The minister said that the national economic operations in 
the country in the first quarter this year was on the whole 
good. Some problems and difficulties, however, still appeared 
including the unsatisfactory sales of production means and a 
drop in economic results in enterprises specializing in 
commodity circulation. Some of these problems and difficulties 
resulted from certain temporary factors and were undergoing a 
solution through measures taken by relevant state departments. 
  Mr. Zhang called for departments and units under the 
ministry 
to keep a close eye on and analyze market changes and trends 
especially for important goods related to people's livelihood 
and at the same time adopt respective measures to control and 
regulate such changes and trends. 
  Mr. Zhang pointed out that the current work for the ministry 
was the purchase of summer grain and edible oil, the easing of 
supply of these products, the supply of chemical fertilizers, 
the earnest implementation of state price policies, prevention 
increased burdens imposed on farmers and the rectification of 
the market order of agricultural production means. [sentence as 
received] 

</TEXT>

