<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Small, Medium-Sized Firms' Goods `Low Quality' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Small, Medium-Sized Firms' Goods `Low Quality' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1105072694 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1325 GMT 
10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1105072694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 10 (CNS) -- The State Bureau of 
Technological Supervision has found the quality of products of 
large-sized enterprises improved but those from medium- and 
small-scale and township enterprises were still producing 
counterfeit and low quality products. 
  Some 954 of medium and small-sized enterprises were 
examined, 
making up 82.5 percent of the total enterprises looked at. Of 
these, only 63.7 percent of the products were found to meet the 
standards and only 62.7 percent of township enterprise products 
were found to meet the standards, and at the same time, the 
production of counterfeit and low quality products remained 
serious. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-49866 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi091_n_94012" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-091 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  11 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rural Firms Record 47 Percent Growth </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rural Firms Record 47 Percent Growth </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1105041194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0318 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1105041194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 11 (XINHUA) -- China's rural firms had 
an output worth 474 billion yuan in the first quarter of this 
year -- a 47 percent growth over the same period of last year, 
said the Ministry of Agriculture. 
  The ministry officials said this formed a sharp contrast 
with 
the state-owned sector, which chalked up a growth of only 2.2 
percent during the first three months. 
  The officials estimated that rural industries will have an 
annual growth of 25 percent to 30 percent this year. 
  Meanwhile, rural firms have seen a remarkable improvement in 
their product quality, thanks to an investment of more than 100 
billion yuan in fixed assets last year, mainly for improving 
manufacturing technology. 
  Facing market competition that is getting fiercer and 
fiercer, the rural firms have been improving their management 
and adopting a flexible market policy, the officials noted. 
  In the first quarter of this year rural firms sold more than 
83 percent of the products made during that period, making a 
sales income of 395 billion yuan. 
  In the first three months the exports of rural firms 
skyrocketed by 72 percent over the same period of last year, to 
reach 48.5 billion yuan. 
  According to the officials, rural firms now employ one tenth 
of the nation's population. In 1993 alone the number of their 
employees increased by six million. 
  The officials said they expect that rural firms will be able 
to absorb more surplus rural labor. The government estimates 
that China will have five million more people in need of jobs by 
the end of this year. 
  The officials said rural firms in Anhui, Jiangxi, Henan and 
Sichuan Provinces and the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region 
showed the fastest growth in the first quarter. 
  Rural industrial enterprises in east China reported a 50 
percent growth in the first three months, three percentage 
points higher than the national average in the same period, the 
officials added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

