BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 12 (XINHUA) -- The remark made by the 
U.S. Assistant Secretary Winston Lord at the Senate Subcommittee 
of Foreign Relations is totally groundless, said a Chinese 
Foreign Ministry spokesman here today. 
  At a weekly press conference here this afternoon, Spokesman 
Wu Jianmin made the statement when asked to comment on a report 
that on May 4, Lord indicated at the Senate Subcommittee of 
Foreign Relations that China in the past possibly aided the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea's ballistic missile 
program, and surely helped its nuclear program. 
  Wu said "such a remark is totally groundless and entirely 
irresponsible". 

