positive progress since Russian President Boris Yeltsin visited 
China in December 1992. 
  The purpose of the coming visit by the Russian prime 
minister 
is to "promote the steady and sustained development of bilateral 
relations on the basis of the achievements already made, 
especially to further promote the two countries' economic and 
trade cooperation", the spokesman said. 

