<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-092 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Notes IAEA To Send New Inspection Team to DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    XINHUA Notes IAEA To Send New Inspection Team to DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1205022094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0158 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1205022094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, May 11 (XINHUA) -- The International Atomic 
Energy Agency (IAEA) announced today that it will send a mission 
to the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) on Saturday 
[14 May] to continue its inspection of the DPRK's nuclear 
facilities. 
  Tests will be conducted at a reprocessing plant if the DPRK 
government gives a positive reply or does not raise any 
objection to the move before the weekend, IAEA Spokesman David 
Kyd said. 
  IAEA Director General Hans Blix said in a message sent to 
DPRK Foreign Minister Kim Yong-nam on Tuesday that it was 
crucial for international experts to inspect spent uranium fuel 
rods at the nuclear reactor when the plant is refueled. 
  Blix also requested the DPRK to send a team of experts to 
Vienna to discuss measures and a timetable for inspections of 
the reactor. 
  Last week, an IAEA spokesman said last week that the agency 
will not send inspectors to the DPRK until the government gives 
the green light to an overall inspection of its nuclear 
facilities. 

</TEXT>

