<H3> <TI>   Envoy Chen Shiqiu Addresses UN Narcotics Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Envoy Chen Shiqiu Addresses UN Narcotics Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1205045594 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1410 
GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1205045594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Zhang Hao (1728 3185)] </F>
  [Text] Vienna, 21 Apr (XINHUA) -- The 37th conference of 
the UN Commission on Narcotic Drugs concluded in Vienna on 21 
April. 
  The conference deliberated the work of the UN Drug 
Prohibition Agency and International Narcotics Control Bureau, 
emphatically studied and drew up new measures against 
drug-related crimes, and passed a series of resolutions on 
issues such as prohibiting the illegal production, trafficking, 
and consumption of drugs. 
  Delegates to the conference also deliberated the resolution 
passed by the 48th UN General Assembly last year on drug 
prohibition and exchanged views on the present situation of drug 
dealing in the world, and the implementation of drug prohibition 
conventions by different countries. Chen Shiqiu, head of the 
Chinese delegation and Chinese permanent representative to the 
UN office and other international organizations in Vienna, spoke 
at the conference. He expounded the important measures and 
achievements in China's crackdown on drug-related crimes over 
recent years. The content of his speech won the attention and 
affirmation of fellow delegates at the conference. 
  The conference opened on 13 April. 

</TEXT>

