<H3> <TI>   Sino-U.S. Antidumping Legal Provisions Symposium Held </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sino-U.S. Antidumping Legal Provisions Symposium Held </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1105153494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1501 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1105153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 11 (XINHUA) -- A Sino-U.S. symposium on 
anti-dumping legal provisions, the first of its kind in China, 
opened Monday [9 May] in Beijing. 
  Experts from the Commerce Department of the United States 
will introduce the U.S. legal provisions on anti-dumping to 
Chinese participants during the 10-day symposium. 
  Officials from foreign trade and economic cooperation 
committees in China and more than 100 representatives from 
enterprises in northern and northeastern China are attending the 
symposium. 
  The symposium is expected to give Chinese personnel engaged 
in foreign trade a better idea about the legal provisions on 
anti-dumping in the United States as well as anti-dumping 
tendencies in the world, said Wang Dianguo, an official from the 
Chinese Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation. 
  It will also help strengthen the management of Chinese 
exports, he added. 
  The symposium will hold further discussions in Shanghai and 
Guangzhou. 

</TEXT>

