<H3> <TI>   Hubei Imports U.S. Boiler Island </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hubei Imports U.S. Boiler Island </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0605184794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1443 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0605184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 6 (XINHUA) -- The China National 
Technical Import and Export Corporation (CNTIC) signed a 
contract here today with the U.S. Foster wheeler energy company 
to import a boiler island worth 190 million U.S. dollars. 
  The island is being imported for the Ezhou Power Station, 30 
km east of Wuhan, capital of Hubei Province. 
  The power station, composed of two sets of turbogenerators 
with a capacity of 300,000 kilowatts each, is the first thermal 
power plant built with part of the third batch of loans from the 
Japanese Government. 
  The station is made up of a boiler island, turbine island 
and 
a electrical equipment island. 
  Last March, CNTIC signed contracts with Japan's Itochu 
Corporation and ABB Ltd. to import a turbine island and an 
electrical equipment island worth 130 million U.S. dollars. 
  Last year, the Foster Wheeler Energy Company exported a 
boiler island to Zouxian Power Station in east China's Shandong 
Province. 
  The construction of the Ezhou Power Station will help ease 
electricity shortages in Hubei Province, CNTIC sources said. 

</TEXT>

