<H3> <TI>   Li Ruihuan Holds Talks With Norwegian Prime Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Li Ruihuan Holds Talks With Norwegian Prime Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1105162994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1604 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1105162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Oslo, May 11 (XINHUA) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the 
national committee of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), held talks here today with 
Norwegian Acting Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Bjorn Tore 
Godal on joint efforts to promote cooperation between China and 
Norway. 
  Li Ruihuan briefed Godal on China's current economic 
construction and the democratic politics. 
  He said democracy marks the advance of a society, it is also 
the inevitable trend of history. The Chinese government 
maintains that the building of democratic politics actively and 
steadily must be on the basis of social stability. Otherwise, 
he said, it will hurt society and even create social chaos. 
  Godal said that Norway gives great importance to relations 
with China which has world influence. 
  He said he is pleased to see the rapid development of 
Sino-Norwegian cooperation in trade, science and other fields. 

</TEXT>

