<F P=100> East Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   Polish Prime Minister Receives PLA's Zhang Wannian </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Polish Prime Minister Receives PLA's Zhang Wannian </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1205043394 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0436 
GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1205043394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Wang Defeng (3769 1795 7685)] </F>
  [Text] Warsaw, 9 May (XINHUA) -- On the morning of 9 May, 
Polish Prime Minister Waldeman Pawlak met with General Zhang 
Wannian, member of the Central Military Commission and chief of 
General Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army [PLA], and 
his party who are currently visiting Poland. 
  Pawlak was pleased with the development of Sino-Polish 
bilateral cooperative relations in the military field. He said 
Poland hopes to establish a cooperative partnership with China, 
particularly in the economic field. 
  According to Pawlak's briefing, Poland has now entered a 
period of normal development after experiencing acute changes. 
Located in central Eastern Europe, Poland can serve as a bridge 
for developing China's contacts with Western European countries. 
  Zhang Wannian said that Chinese leaders and the government 
attach great importance to developing friendly relations and 
cooperation with Poland and the Polish Army; and the purpose of 
his current visit is to deepen understanding and enhance 
friendship to promote the development of relations between the 
two countries and two armies. 
  After winding up a trip to Romania, Zhang Wannian and his 
party arrived in Warsaw on 7 May for this visit. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

