<H3> <TI>   Symposium Held on Sino-Latin American Sci-Tech Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Symposium Held on Sino-Latin American Sci-Tech Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1005044594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0159 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1005044594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Changsha, May 10 (XINHUA) -- A symposium on 
scientific and technological cooperation between China and Latin 
America was held recently in Changsha, capital of central 
China's Hunan Province. 
  People from Chinese research institutes and provincial and 
municipal committees of science and technology attended the 
symposium. 
  China has diplomatic relations with 17 countries in Latin 
America and has trade relations with 33 Latin American countries 
and 13 regions. 
  The total trade volume between China and Latin American 
countries amounted to nearly three billion U.S. dollars last 
year. 
  Since 1988, the two sides have been undertaking nearly 100 
cooperation programs every year. 
  The scientific and technological cooperation not only 
deepens 
the mutual understanding of the scientists from the two sides 
but also benefits their economic construction. 

</TEXT>

