<H3> <TI>   Bolivian Group Expects To Enhance Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bolivian Group Expects To Enhance Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1105153794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1443 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1105153794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Zhanjiang, May 11 (XINHUA) -- A group of Bolivian 
visitors headed by H. Alfonso Ferrufino Valderrama, 
vice-president of Bolivia's Chamber of Deputies, said that they 
will take Zhanjiang as a base to enhance economic and trade 
cooperation between Bolivia and China. 
  Situated on the Leizhou Peninsula in Guangdong Province, 
Zhanjiang city is one of eight major sea ports in China. 
  During their business tour in Zhanjiang city, the Bolivian 
guests visited Nansan Island near the city. 
  The island occupies 123.4 square kilometers with 34 percent 
of its land covered with forests. 
  The Bolivian guests consider the island an ideal place for 
establishing a trade base between Bolivia and China. 
  Eduardo la Fuente Roca, general manager of the Industrial 
and 
Commercial Chamber of Cochabamba of Bolivia, said that the base 
will provide an opportunity for businessmen in Latin American 
countries to engage in free trade and entrepot trade. 
  He said that his chamber has sent letters to related Chinese 
departments to apply to establish of a business center in 
Zhanjiang city. 
  The Bolivian businessmen also expressed their intention to 
invest in flower raising and refined processing of livestock 
products. 

</TEXT>

