<H3> <TI>   Chen Yun, Others Write Inscription for Army Monument </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chen Yun, Others Write Inscription for Army Monument </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1205011194 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1327 
GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1205011194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter He Maoji (0149 2021 4921)] </F>
  [Excerpts] Kunming, 9 May (XINHUA) -- [passage omitted] 
The "Monument of the Red Army Crossing the River," whose title 
was inscribed by Comrade Chen Yun and which stands on the bank 
of the Jinsha Jiang at the Jiaoping ferry crossing in Luquan 
County, Yunnan Province, has been completed. Today, over 1,000 
people of all nationalities from the two provinces of Yunnan and 
Sichuan gathered at a ceremony to unveil the monument. [passage 
omitted] 
  The monument was built along the riverside. Its height is 
18.85 meter [m] and width 24 m, and it is shaped like a pyramid. 
On the top-most part of the monument stand the bronze statues 
of Red Armymen baring the upper parts of their bodies and 
holding up oars. Comrades Liu Huaqing, Zhang Zhen, Xiao Ke, and 
Yang Chengwu wrote inscriptions for the monument. 

</TEXT>

