<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seventh Meeting of NPC Standing Committee Closes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seventh Meeting of NPC Standing Committee Closes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1205100794 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 0505 
GMT 12 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1205100794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Chinese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 12 May (XINHUA) -- The eight-day-long 
Seventh Meeting of the Eighth National People's Congress [NPC] 
Standing Committee closed at the Great Hall of the People this 
morning after it voted in five laws and approved appointments 
and removals by vote. 
  Chairman Qiao Shi presided at this morning's meeting. 
  The following are the five laws adopted one-by-one by vote 
at 
this meeting: The Foreign Trade Law, the State Compensation 
Law, the NPC Standing Committee Decision on Amendments to the 
Regulations Governing Offenses Against Public Order, the NPC 
Standing Committee Decision on Amendments to the Chinese 
People's Liberation Army [PLA] Regulations Governing the 
Military Service of Officers in Active Duty, and the NPC 
Standing Committee Decision on PLA Regulations Governing 
Officers' Ranks [title as received]. 
  State President Jiang Zemin today signed separate 
presidential decrees, Nos. 22, 23, 24, 25, and 26, to promulgate 
these five laws. 
  The Foreign Trade Law consists of eight chapters covering 44 
articles, including: general principles, foreign trade 
operators, import and export of cargoes and technological 
exports, international service trades, foreign trade orders, 
promotion of foreign trade, legal responsibility, and addenda. 
This law will take effect on 1 July 1994. 
  The State Compensation Law consists of six chapters covering 
35 articles, including: general principles, administrative 
compensation, criminal compensation, compensation methods and 
standards for calculation, other stipulations, and addendum. 
This law will take effect on 1 January 1995. 
  The meeting decided by vote to add 13 people, including Wang 
Yingwei [3769 5391 0251], as members to the Preliminary Working 
Committee of the Preparatory Committee of the Hong Kong Special 
Administrative Region, and appointed Nie Li [5119 0500] a member 
of the NPC Internal and Judicial Affairs Committee. The meeting 
also adopted other lists of appointments and removals. 
  A motion made to the NPC Standing Committee by the State 
Council to appoint three ministers was adopted at the meeting 
today: The meeting voted to relieve Zhu Xun of his duties as 
minister of geology and mineral resources, and appoint Song 
Ruixiang to the post; to relieve Ai Zhisheng of his duties as 
minister of radio, cinema, and television, and appoint Sun 
Jiazheng to the post; to relieve Lu Peijian of his duties as 
auditor general of the Auditing Administration, and appoint Gu 
Zhenqian to the post. 
  The meeting made preliminary examination of and deliberated 
on a report on progress made in preparations for the Three 
Gorges Project. 
  Attending the meeting were Vice Chairmen Wang Hanbin, Ni 
Zhifu, Chen Muhua, Fei Xiaotong, Sun Qimeng, Lei Jieqiong, Qin 
Jiwei, Li Ximing, Wang Bingqian, Wang Guangying, Cheng Siyuan, 
Lu Jiaxi, Buhe, Tomur Dawamat, Li Peiyao, and Wu Jieping, and 
Secretary General Cao Zhi. 
  State Councillor Li Tieying; Ren Jianxin, Supreme People's 
Court president; and Zhang Siqing, procurator general of the 
Supreme People's Procuratorate, attended the meeting as 
observers. 

</TEXT>

