<H3> <TI>   `Religious' Activist Zhang Ruiyu Released on Parole </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Religious' Activist Zhang Ruiyu Released on Parole </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1205031194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0305 GMT 12 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1205031194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 12 (XINHUA) -- Zhang Ruiyu, who was 
convicted in August 1990 of having conspired to overthrow the 
government by means of religious activities, has been released 
on parole, sources said here today. 
  Zhang was sentenced to a term of imprisonment by the Putian 
city Intermediate People's Court of Fujian Province. 
  The court recently ruled according to law that as she had 
abided by prison regulations and had behaved well during her 
imprisonment, she was qualified for release on parole. 

</TEXT>

