<H3> <TI>   Chen Jinhua on Economic Information Network </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chen Jinhua on Economic Information Network </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1205060194 Beijing Central People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2230 GMT 24 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1205060194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing Central People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News and Press Review" program] </F>
  [Text] Speaking yesterday [24 April] at the 1994 work 
conference of the state economic information network, Chen 
Jinhua, minister in charge of the State Planning Commission, 
noted: The state economic information network should seize the 
opportunity to deepen reform, play its role, harness its 
potential, and better serve the twin information needs of the 
government and society. 
  Chen Jinhua said: The state economic information network was 
established in 1984 with the State Council's approval. In the 
eight years or so since its inception, the network has expanded 
to cover the entire country. More than 30 provinces, autonomous 
regions, and municipalities directly under the central 
government; all cities with provincial-level economic 
decisionmaking power; 280 key cities and regions; and 1,500 
counties have become information hubs sufficiently outfitted 
with technology and equipment, and staffed by professional teams. 
  The network has played an important role in serving the 
party 
and government in macroeconomic policy-making, macroeconomic 
regulation and control, and macroeconomic management, as well as 
in providing information to enterprises and people in society. 
  At the conference, Gao Xingmin, director of the State 
Information Center, reviewed last year's achievements, discussed 
new problems, and laid down several key tasks for this year. 

</TEXT>

