<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shandong Reports on Foreign Investment Environment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shandong Reports on Foreign Investment Environment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1205075794 Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1205075794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shandong Province has vigorously strengthened the 
building of infrastructure facilities by giving consideration to 
the interests of foreign traders, thus creating a fine 
environment for foreign countries to run plants and do business 
in the province. Over the past several years, thanks to the 
implementation of the strategy of promoting the development of 
the entire economy with an export-oriented economy, Shandong's 
opening up has extended from eastern coastal areas to western 
inland areas, and the new pattern of opening to all directions 
and levels has taken shape basically. Thus far, eight cities and 
prefectures and 56 counties, cities, and districts have been 
delimited as the coastal economic open region, with its area 
accounting for 40 percent of the province's total territory, its 
population accounting for 38 percent of the province's total, 
and its GNP accounting for 61.8 percent of the province's total. 
Now, this coastal economic open region has become one of the 
largest open regions in China's eastern coastal areas. Qingdao, 
Yantai, and Weihai economic and technological development zones 
have given rise to the new framework of modernized cities. Nine 
high and new technology industrial development zones in Jinan, 
Weihai, and some other localities have begun to take shape and 
become the areas where high science and technology industries 
develop in a concentrated manner. 
  According to statistics, in 1993 the province set a record 
high in utilizing foreign funds, with the foreign funds utilized 
equal to the total in the previous 14 years. In 1993, the 
number of newly approved projects using foreign funds surpassed 
8,000, the amount of contracted foreign funds reached $7.55 
billion, and the foreign funds actually utilized reached $2.26 
billion, respectively showing an increase of 73 percent, 81 
percent, and 83 percent over 1992. Among the projects using 
foreign funds, the projects with optimized structure, high 
grades, large amount of investment, advanced technology, and 
close connections with industries increased obviously. Of them, 
the projects using more than $10 million each numbered 257. 
  Thus far, 65 countries and regions in the world have 
invested 
in Shandong, and the foreign investment sphere has extended to 
commerce, retail sales, and finance. Yamaguchi Bank in Japan 
and (Huifeng) Bank in Hong Kong have opened their banking organs 
in Qingdao. (Xiri) Bank and (Rixin) Stock Company in Japan, 
(Baosheng) Corporation in Hong Kong, (Bada) Corporation in the 
Britain, and the Long-Term Credit Bank in the ROK have 
established representative offices in Shandong. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

