<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangdong Releases First-Quarter Trade Statistics </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Guangdong Releases First-Quarter Trade Statistics </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1205073194 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1205073194 </F>
<F P=104>  Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the Guangdong Customhouse, our 
province was bullish about its import and export trade in the 
first quarter of this year. The total value of our province's 
import and export trade in this quarter amounted to about $16.2 
billion. Both imports and exports increased by more than 20 
percent over the same period last year, with a favorable import 
balance of $150 million, thus putting an end to last year's 
export deficit situation. In export-volume terms, Shenzhen 
ranked first among other cities in the province, with an export 
volume of $3.1 billion; Guangzhou ranked second, with an export 
volume of close to $1.1 billion, and Dongguan City ranked third, 
with an export volume of $1 billion. Shenzhen, Dongguan, and 
Guangzhou were the three top importing cities in our province. 
  In Guangdong's foreign trade, exports exceeded imports in 
the 
first quarter of this year, indicating that after the state 
unified exchange rates this year, import demand, which has 
remained high for many years, had been initially alleviated. 
Meanwhile, as state export encouragement measures, such as duty 
refunds, were further implemented, general export trade began to 
bottom out and gained upward momentum. 

</TEXT>

