<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shenzhen To Experiment With Modern Enterprise System </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shenzhen To Experiment With Modern Enterprise System </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1105122594 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 0400 GMT 9 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1105122594 </F>
<F P=104>  Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Mandarin </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the Shenzhen Commission for 
Restructuring Economy, the city soon will conduct comprehensive 
experiments in 20 selected enterprises on the establishment of a 
modern enterprise system. It will open up a new path by summing 
up the experience gained in these experiments and lay a 
foundation for the city to be the first in the country to 
establish a market economy structure. The main contents of these 
experiments include the establishment of the enterprise 
legal-person system, the limited liability system, and the 
scientific management system; the effective solution of such 
crucial problems as property, personnel, and distribution 
rights; and the adoption of appropriate supporting measures. 
While carrying out these experiments, the city will continue to 
do a good job in the work in three ways: 
  1. The city will reappraise the stocks and assets of 
enterprises, register their property rights, harmonize property 
rights relationships, and institute and perfect an enterprise 
legal-person system. 
  2. It will reform and improve the enterprise internal 
leadership system, and will set up boards of shareholders and 
boards of directors, as well as a scientific leadership 
structure of checks and balances -- under which functions and 
powers are clearly defined -- between [words indistinct]. 
  3. It will improve the enterprise distribution system and 
set up a rational encouragement mechanism. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

