<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meeting Between Taiwan, Zambian Presidents Denied </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meeting Between Taiwan, Zambian Presidents Denied </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1105135294 Taipei CNA in English 1307 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1105135294 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Bear Li] </F>
  [Text] Pretoria, May 11 (CNA) -- The Republic of China 
[ROC]'s ambassador to South Africa, Loh I-cheng, on Wednesday 
[11 May] denied reports that President Li Teng-hui had a dinner 
meeting with Zambia President Frederick Chiluba during which the 
two discussed establishing diplomatic relations. 
  Several Taipei newspapers carried reports Wednesday that 
Chiluba was the guest of honor at a dinner given by Li at Loh's 
residence Tuesday. Both President Li and Chiluba were among the 
heads of state attending the inauguration of new South African 
President Nelson Mandela. 
  Loh and Presidential Spokesman Raymond Tai, who is 
accompanying Li during his trip, said only embassy staff and 
President Li's entourage were present at the dinner. 
  But Loh said Li did have a meeting with ranking South 
African 
officials, including a provincial governor and a member of the 
new cabinet, at his residence Tuesday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-49964 </DOCNO>
