<H3> <TI>   High Court Upholds Ruling on Mainland Hijacker </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    High Court Upholds Ruling on Mainland Hijacker </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1105141294 Taipei CNA in English 1309 GMT 11 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1105141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Benjamin Yeh] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, May 11 (CNA) -- The Taiwan High Court on 
Wednesday [11 May] upheld the nine-year jail term meted out to 
Shih Yuebo by the Taipei District Court earlier this year for 
hijacking a passenger airliner from Mainland China to Taiwan on 
Aug. 10. 
  Shih pled not guilty, claiming he hijacked the plane to seek 
political asylum mere. 
  Shih, 30, of Hebei Province, forced the Air China Boeing 
767, 
which was en route from Beijing to Indonesia, to land in Taiwan 
after he threatened the crew with what he said was a bomb but 
that later turned out to be sulfuric acid in a bottle. 
  Nobody was injured during the incident, the third of 11 
hijackings of mainland Chinese planes to Taiwan last year. 

</TEXT>

