  [Text] Beijing, May 10 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-President 
Rong Yiren met here today with Philip Leigh Tose, chairman of 
the Hong Kong Peregrine Investments Holdings Limited. 
  Rong said that expansion of China's opening up is an 
important aspect of its economic development, in the process of 
which China needs to attract foreign investments as well as 
upgrade its technology and reform old enterprises, through 
introduction of international advanced science and technology 
and management. 
  He expressed hope that Peregrine would play its role in 
China's economic construction and forge closer ties with Chinese 
enterprises both in the mainland and in Hong Kong. 
  Tose, who is leading a party here to attend the 1994 China 
summit meeting scheduled to open tomorrow, said that the future 
of his firm is closely related to the future of China. 
  "China will play a bigger role in the world in the next 
century," he noted. "We are full of confidence in the future of 
Hong Kong." 

