<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fujian Regulates Prices of Daily Necessities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fujian Regulates Prices of Daily Necessities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1105134694 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0818 GMT 
11 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1105134694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Fuzhou, May 11 (CNS)--Fujian's provincial 
government has decided to regulate prices of nine categories of 
daily necessities and 50 basic services to curb inflation there. 
  The nine categories of daily necessities include grain, 
edible oil, meat and poultry, eggs, aquatic products, fresh 
vegetables, seasonings, milk and milk products as well as 
household articles. 
  The provincial government has stipulated that among these 
categories, adjustment to the prices set by the government must 
be reported to a high-level authority for filing, while the 
adjustment to other prices which had been regulated by market 
forces must be reported to the relevant department for 
examination five days ahead of implementation of the adjustment. 
  The government has also asked authorities at various levels 
there to set up and improve the system of reserving important 
foods such as grain, edible oil and meat as well as grain risk 
funds and the strengthening of macro-control and adjustment of 
prices of non-staple foods. [sentence as received] Those found 
breaching regulations will be seriously dealt with. 

</TEXT>

