<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Authorities Release 5 `Offenders' Early </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Authorities Release 5 `Offenders' Early </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1305113494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0934 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1305113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 13 (XINHUA) -- Five offenders were 
recently released from education-through-labor institutions 
before their terms expire, according to a department concerned 
here. 
  Chen Zhuman, Yan Peizhi, Xu Zhihe, Cui Tai and Zhang Li were 
ordered to be re-educated through labor respectively between 
December 1991 and September 1993 because of disturbing social 
order and endangering public security by making use of religion. 
  Decisions to release them were made by the 
eduction-through-labor committees of Quanzhou City in Fujian 
Province, Weifang City in Shandong Province and Zhangjiakou City 
in Hebei Province. The department concerned said that they were 
released ahead of time because they had been amenable to 
discipline and behaved themselves during correctional period. 

</TEXT>

