<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Taipei To Work With ASEAN Nations on IPR </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Taipei To Work With ASEAN Nations on IPR </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1305085594 Taipei CNA in English 0756 GMT 13 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1305085594 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Debbie Kuo] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, May 13 (CNA) -- Taiwan will work with 
Southeast Asian countries to increase regional intellectual 
property rights (IPR) protection, the Board of Foreign Trade 
(BOFT) said Friday [13 May]. 
  Taiwan is paying equal attention to consultations on both 
IPR 
protection and agricultural imports as part of its effort to 
join the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade (GATT), BOFT 
officials said. 
  The efforts include exchanges of information and personnel 
between Taiwan and members of the Association of Southeast Asian 
Nations (ASEAN). 
  Besides IPR protection consultations, the officials said, 
BOFT is seeking bilateral recognition of national laboratories 
and cooperation in product verification and quality control 
certification with ASEAN members. 
  Details of the issues will be further discussed in an 
October 
Asia-Pacific meterology conference to be held in Taipei, BOFT 
said. 

</TEXT>

