<F P=106> [From "News at One" program] </F>
  [Text] China has criticized the American Assistant 
Secretary of State Winston Lord for planning to meet a released 
Chinese dissident. Mr. Lord has agreed to have talks in 
Washington later today with the dissident, Wang Juntao, who was 
sentenced to 13 years in jail but was allowed to leave China 
last month for medical treatment. A Chinese Foreign Ministry 
spokesman said his government opposed anyone carrying out 
political activity against China by making use of Wang Juntao. 

