<H3> <TI>   Warren Christopher Holds Talks With Syrian President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Warren Christopher Holds Talks With Syrian President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1505212794 Beijing XINHUA in English 2040 GMT 15 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1505212794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Damascus, May 15 (XINHUA) -- Syrian President Hafiz 
al- Asad today met with visiting U.S. Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher who arrived here earlier today on a new tour of the 
Middle East. 
  Syrian Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' went to Damascus 
airport to greet the U.S. official, whose ongoing tour aims at 
securing an essential progress in the Syrian-Israeli peace talks 
in Washington. 
  Israel's proposals on the return of the occupied Golan 
Heights is believed to be the main topic in talks between 
Christopher and al- Asad. 
  Israel has offered a phased withdrawal from the Golan 
Heights 
but did not give details on how much territory it planed to 
return to Syria. At the same time, Israel wanted to set up full 
diplomatic relations with Syria. 
  Syria demanded Israel's commitment to a full withdrawal 
before outlining its stand on future relations. 
  On the eve of Christopher's tour to the region, the Arab 
world called for Israel's complete withdrawal from the occupied 
Golan Heights, stressing that peace will not be achieved unless 
it facilitates a comprehensive pullout based on international 
legitimacy and in line [with] relevant U.N. Security Council 
resolutions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

